Between the Yevre and the Auron was a plateau, some 1200 toss1600 feet high, with rather steep bankS. As this plateau approached the town, it narrowed to a ridge only about 400 feet wide, with the Auron on one side and a swampy brook, the Ye'vrette, on the other. From the Ye'vrette to the Yevre extended a morass.
